round-color: #ccc;">U.S. sanctions</a> since 2014, it has been a menacing n=
eighbor for some time now, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0there is some risk that=C2=
=A0<em>any=C2=A0</em>country that issues dollar bonds might not have the do=
llars to pay them back. Of course the country might just not pay=C2=A0<em>a=
nything=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0instead of giving you rubles it could give=
 you nothing =E2=80=94=C2=A0but there is some chance that for face-saving o=
r helping-local-investors reasons it might give you its local currency inst=
ead and say =E2=80=9Chey, we paid you, what=E2=80=99s the problem.=E2=80=9D=
