ZGMw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf38221c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">seize=C2=A0an Argentine nav=
al vessel</a>. That's a fun lark for a hedge fund! Trying to seize a Russia=
n naval vessel is not.[2]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Realistically the=
 best you can do, if Russia decides to pay you in rubles, is say =E2=80=9Ct=
his has been a=C2=A0terrible experience and=C2=A0I am never going to lend m=
oney to Russia again!=E2=80=9D To the extent this is true =E2=80=94=C2=A0to=
 the extent it=E2=80=99s a credible threat =E2=80=94 it will deter Russia f=
rom paying you in rubles; Russia wants to be able to issue international bo=
nds. But of course countries do default on their sovereign debt from time t=
